parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to maneuver, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering assist fails to operate
the steering wheel vibrates or clunks
the vehicle is hard to steer
the power steering warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle jerks forward and swerves before coming to a stop
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brakes make a squeaking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks forward and swerves before coming to a stop
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brakes make a squeaking noise
the engine light stays on due to a gas cap error (even though the vehicle has a cap-less tank).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and potentially fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle jerks forward and swerves before coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering angle sensor can cause the vehicle to lock up, preventing acceleration and steering, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates the engine but does not move
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle turns on in the middle of traffic without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the vehicle to go into limp mode, resulting in a loss of power while traveling at any speed, which can be dangerous for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode
the vehicle loses all power while traveling at any speed
the throttle body is considered closed by the SUV's computer despite being clean and functioning properly.
